## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/application-shell.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

For global behavior and state contracts, also consult `Logic.md` (state management, VPN lifecycle) at the project root.

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/application-shell.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` | Exports `MapLayerOption` used for `selectedMapLayer` state |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Sole owner of global state: `selectedCountry`, `selectedMapLayer`, `vpnStatus`, `connectedCountry`, `physicalCountry`, `panelWidth` (see feature doc table).
- Connect flow: 3s timer to `protected`; clear timer on disconnect or new connect (`Logic.md`).
- No duplicate copies of `selectedCountry` in children — single source of truth in `App`.

## Patterns to Follow

- Prop drilling only; `useCallback` / `useRef` for handlers and connect timer.
- Panel resize: pointer events on document, width clamped 200–400px.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT duplicate shared utilities or UI that already lives in `src/app/components/ui/`, `src/app/components/layerData.ts`, `countryData.ts`, or `src/imports/` — extend or import instead. (This repo has no `src/shared/` directory.)
- Do NOT modify files outside `src/app/App.tsx` without following `/docs/features/_overview.md` and getting explicit approval for cross-feature changes.
- Do NOT add URL routes — none are defined; the app is a single-page shell (`_overview.md`).
- Do NOT change global state field names or meanings without updating `/docs/features/application-shell.md`, `Logic.md`, and all consumers listed in `_overview.md`.
